presentation this morning,

00:04:17.750 --> 00:04:20.930
it was actually mentioned that
really low ratings are often

00:04:20.930 --> 00:04:23.930
caused by technical stability.

00:04:23.930 --> 00:04:25.460
Number two was actually spot on.

00:04:25.460 --> 00:04:28.850
It's insufficient
value proposition.

00:04:28.850 --> 00:04:32.840
So the product is just not
there or it's not good enough.

00:04:32.840 --> 00:04:35.990
The third one is, maybe
the product is good enough

00:04:35.990 --> 00:04:38.190
but you're not making
it clear to the user.

00:04:38.190 --> 00:04:41.953
So it's not-- they don't really
know how great your product is.

00:04:44.670 --> 00:04:46.920
Or you're just not fresh enough.

00:04:46.920 --> 00:04:48.010
The content is outdated.

00:04:48.010 --> 00:04:49.320
The functionality is outdated.

00:04:49.320 --> 00:04:50.986
You're not keeping
pace with the market.

00:04:53.237 --> 00:04:54.570
Or it's not personalized enough.

00:04:54.570 --> 00:04:56.160
It's too interchangeable, right?

00:04:56.160 --> 00:04:59.280
It's great, but others do
it as well and the user,

00:04:59.280 --> 00:05:00.470
they like to try new things.

00:05:00.470 --> 00:05:02.470
So they go to something
else and they don't know

00:05:02.470 --> 00:05:04.590
why they should be coming back.

00:05:04.590 --> 00:05:07.214
And I think that's a classic.

00:05:07.214 --> 00:05:08.880
You just overdo it
on push notifications

00:05:08.880 --> 00:05:10.290
or general communication.

00:05:10.290 --> 00:05:12.720
That's a classic one as well.

00:05:12.720 --> 00:05:16.860
And many, many more that I
think cause problems and that

00:05:16.860 --> 00:05:18.270
cause you guys headaches.

00:05:18.270 --> 00:05:20.520
