really important

00:08:01.610 --> 00:08:06.440
to have to have
that crystal clear.

00:08:06.440 --> 00:08:10.670
Here are some things,
or some questions,

00:08:10.670 --> 00:08:13.880
that I think you need to
have the right answers to.

00:08:13.880 --> 00:08:15.662
And again, it's not
necessarily only

00:08:15.662 --> 00:08:17.120
you having the
right answers to it,

00:08:17.120 --> 00:08:18.630
but also make sure
these answers are

00:08:18.630 --> 00:08:23.070
known across the various
teams and across the company.

00:08:23.070 --> 00:08:26.340
So first of all,
what is your USP?

00:08:26.340 --> 00:08:28.970
It could be many different
things, depending

00:08:28.970 --> 00:08:30.920
on which vertical you're in.

00:08:30.920 --> 00:08:35.409
If you're a publisher and you
you publish news or stories,

00:08:35.409 --> 00:08:37.159
then the quality of
the story could be one

00:08:37.159 --> 00:08:38.725
of your selling propositions.

00:08:38.725 --> 00:08:40.100
If you're a fitness
app, it could

00:08:40.100 --> 00:08:43.520
be that you motivate your users
very well to actually exercise

00:08:43.520 --> 00:08:47.540
more, and so on.

00:08:47.540 --> 00:08:49.780
That, I think, is the
most important bit.

00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:52.490
But also keep in mind that
your users are usually not

00:08:52.490 --> 00:08:56.120
one homogeneous group, but there
are different user cohorts.

00:08:56.120 --> 00:08:58.790
So there may well
be more than one USP

00:08:58.790 --> 00:09:01.560
that is really important
for your business.

00:09:01.560 --> 00:09:04.760
The second one is, what does
engagement mean for you?

00:09:04.760 --> 00:09:08.600
And as trivial as that
question sounds, really think

00:09:08.600 --> 00:09:12.080
hardly about, what is it
that you want the user to do

00:09:12.080 --> 00:09:15.020
that actually makes them fall
in love with your product

00:09:15.020 --> 00:09:18.410
and come back and actually
start building this relationship

00:09:18.410 --> 00:09:22.730
with you as a developer
or as a product offering?

00:09:22.730 --> 00:09:26.480
And third one, it kind of goes
along with number one or two.

00:09:26.480 --> 00:09:28.490
What are the
corresponding KPI's?

00:09:28.490 --> 00:09:31.027
Like whenever I have
conversations with partners--

00:09:31.027 --> 00:09:33.110
and I think that's probably
the same when you have

00:09:33.110 --> 00:09:36.800
conversations among each other--
you compare a lot of KPI's.

00:09:36.800 --> 00:09:40.460
But it's not necessarily
that the same KPI's

00:09:40.460 --> 00:09:43.790
are as relevant for
everybody in the room, right?

00:09:43.790 --> 00:09:45.780
If you're, let's say,
a document storage

00:09:45.780 --> 00:09:49.700
app that really helps me secure
all my important documents,

00:09:49.700 --> 00:09:52.790
then actually retaining
me over a year

00:09:52.790 --> 00:09:57.055
and having me log in once a year
maybe a super important KPI.

00:09:57.055 --> 00:09:59.180
While if you build a social
app, on the other hand,

00:09:59.180 --> 00:10:03.290
you want to look into sessions
per day that it generates.

00:10:03.290 --> 00:10:06.545
So be really aware of what
KPI's are important to you.

00:10:11.390 --> 00:10:15.650
Number two is, again, I
think a somewhat obvious one,

00:10:15.650 --> 00:10:17.660
but I want to give you
a certain angle to it.

00:10:17.660 --> 00:10:20.740
It's to fully utilize the
potential of the Android

00:10:20.740 --> 00:10:21.990
platform.

00:10:21.990 --> 00:10:24.350
And in the talks this
morning, again, we

00:10:24.350 --> 00:10:27.530
heard a lot from Mark and
from Ellie, and [INAUDIBLE],

00:10:27.530 --> 00:10:29.654
and so on, how much
we are investing

00:10:29.654 --> 00:10:31.820
in making sure that the
platform grows and gives you

00:10:31.820 --> 00:10:35.670
more and more opportunities.

00:10:35.670 --> 00:10:39.920
However, doing this is also
a great way, or a great tool,

00:10:39.920 --> 00:10:43.160
for engagement and retention.

00:10:43.160 --> 00:10:46.700
In one of many great
examples, WeVideo-- it's

00:10:46.700 --> 00:10:51.230
actually a video editing app--
they changed their whole UX

00:10:51.230 --> 00:10:56.630
to material design and were
able to increase user engagement

00:10:56.630 --> 00:11:02.230
by 100% from doing that,
just because the experience

00:11:02.230 --> 00:11:04.820
became so seamless and
understandable and great

00:11:04.820 --> 00:11:06.860
for users.

00:11:06.860 --> 00:11:08.450
And it goes beyond that.

00:11:08.450 --> 00:11:12.110
Adopting stuff like Android
Auto, Android TV, or Android

00:11:12.110 --> 00:11:14.900
Wear can also make
a huge difference

00:11:14.900 --> 00:11:18.775
on how you engage your
users with your app.

